title: Microaudio
description: Premetto, questo è un esperimento per uscire dalla realtà preconfezionata del podcast. Qui ho voluto creare degli audio estemporanei senza che vi fosse un benchè minimo ritocco audio, semplicemente anche un filtro per togliere eventuali riverberi della stanza. Tutto in presa diretta, naturale e spontaneo. La novità sta tutta qui, registrerò questi audio esclusivamente con il cellulare, quindi la qualità sarà quella che sarà, buona, ottima, pessima. Dipenderà dal momento in cui registro e dall'ambiente in cui registro. Il podcast, per quanto io lo concepisca come un prodotto non perfettamente confezionato (come lo sono invece la maggiorparte), tutt'altro, lo interpreto come qualcosa di estremamente spontaneo e non cuarto, come ho sempre dichiarato fin dall'esordio de Il piano sottile. Il podcast è comunque un prodotto vecchio, come i prodotti che le prime radio rilasciavano nei primi decenni della loro esistenza, sono tutti postprodotti e raramente si trovano episodi LIVE in ambienti che non siano una studio radiofocnico o un ambiente acusticamente trattato. Qui invece voglio andare oltre il podcast, che appunto nasce vecchio, qui registrerò solamente pensieri estemporanei in libertà, ma senza ritocco alcuno. La piattaforma (provvisoria credo) che ho scelto è Soundcloud, perchè comunque mi garantisce una certa libertà nell'embedding delle tracce pubblicate, anche se lo spazio è purtroppo limitato. Il mio intento era quello di sfruttare il mio canale Telegram dove pubblicare gli audio e poi incorporarli nel sito, ma sembra al momento che ancora non sia possibile. Accetto critiche e suggerimenti. Buon ascolto.

title: Wylde Style Network
description: After a looonnnggg hiatus, Wylde Style Radio “Unreal Radio” is BACK and has their own Network now! Featuring Stand Up & Shout, Notebook Wagering, Tribe Called Jess, Welcome to Manassas (A Classy Variety Show) and more WYLDE shows to come, WSN will bring the fun back to our “unreal" network…also known as streaming and/or podcasting. We will also be looking to add other fun shows to add to the Wylde Style Network. Contact us if you think you’ve got what it takes to be a show on the Wylde Style Network. Wylde Style Radio got started in 2007 as an add-on to the Wylde Style brand when owner, Jeff Wylde, got together with his good friends Kevin Shafer and Rocky Parrish to form Wylde Style Radio w/ Kevin & Rock. The goal was to get the show on terrestrial radio as “Guy Talk” was what was hot at the time. The problem was, they had no idea how to do that other than trying to work connections and put a demo together. So, after working all their contacts and bringing on AV expert, John Caniford, to try something new at the time called live streaming and podcasting, Wylde Style Radio w/ Kevin & Rock launched it’s first show from studios they built inside of the now defunct Chics-N-Wings. The show was a pioneer in podcasting and streaming as even the major stations hadn’t started doing it at the time. The show was instantly popular but a little to bawdy for management at Chics-N-Wings so they had to rethink their strategy and decided to take the show on the road…in a pink RV. At that time Wylde Style Productions had a pink “party bus” RV for its events. WSR moved into the “Pink Nightmare” and we took the show to the masses, doing live shows from outside of popular local bars and businesses like Hooters, The Rhino, PJ Skiddoos, Good Times Tattoos and more. WSR continued to build their audience until 2009 when Kevin & Rock got the call up to the big leagues, 106.7 The Fan DC. They continued to do their show on various platforms until 2016 when everyone went their separate ways until now, when we decided to “get the band back together” as they say. Now we've evolved into our own network with other "Wylde" shows to boot!

title: The Nothing Show
description:
Welcome to "The Nothing Show," the podcast that skillfully balances humor and seriousness while delving into the intricacies of society and our everyday lives. Join me, your host, as I take you on a unique journey where we discuss the world around us, its quirks, and how it influences our daily experiences.

In each episode of "The Nothing Show," we tackle pressing social issues, cultural phenomena, and the latest happenings that shape our collective existence. Whether it's dissecting political trends, examining the impact of technology, or analyzing societal norms, we dive deep into the topics that affect us all. Through thoughtful discussions and insightful commentary, we explore the ways in which these issues intersect with our lives, shedding light on their significance.

But don't be fooled by the seriousness—this show knows how to have fun! "The Nothing Show" is designed to be an entertaining and engaging escape from the mundane. Expect witty banter, humorous anecdotes, and lighthearted segments that provide a refreshing break from the seriousness of the world. It's the perfect blend of laughter and introspection, creating an enjoyable listening experience for those seeking a respite from their day-to-day routine.

Think of "The Nothing Show" as your personal venting session. As your host, I share my own thoughts, frustrations, and observations about the world, creating a safe space for listeners to relate, empathize, and join in on the conversation. Whether it's a hilarious encounter with a self-checkout machine or a serious discussion about the impact of social media on mental health, we explore both the trivial and profound aspects of life, giving a voice to the things we all experience but rarely discuss.

This podcast is for everyone who enjoys thought-provoking conversations, witty humor, and relatable rants. Whether you're commuting, taking a break, or just looking for something to pass the time, "The Nothing Show" is here to keep you company. So sit back, relax, and let's embark on this rollercoaster of laughter, introspection, and everything in between.

Remember, life is full of moments that may seem like nothing at first glance, but hold profound meaning. In "The Nothing Show," we celebrate the mundane, find humor in the chaos, and shed light on the profound implications of the seemingly insignificant. It's a podcast that invites you to laugh, reflect, and be a part of the ever-changing tapestry of our society. Welcome to "The Nothing Show"—where talking about everything and nothing specific is the heart and soul of our captivating journey together.
